Follow these detailed instructions to install the Minecraft AI Bots client on PC or Mac.

<Tabs>
    <Tab title="On Windows" icon="windows">
        1. **Download the Installer** from [here](https://elefant.gg/win) <Icon icon="windows" />

        2. **Run the Installer**
            - Open the downloaded installer file. You will be greeted with the following screen:
            ![Windows Installer][win_installer]
            - Click Next to proceed.

        3. **Choose Install Location**
            - Select the directory where you want to install the client.
            - Click Install. Note that you may need administrator rights to install it.

        4. **Complete Installation**
            - Once the installation is complete, you can run the Launcher.

    </Tab>
    <Tab title="On Mac" icon="apple">
        1. **Download the Installer** from [here](https://elefant.gg/mac) <Icon icon="apple" />

        2. **Open the Installer file**

            You will be greeted with the following screen:
            ![Mac Installer][mac_installer]

        3. **Complete Installation**
            - Once the installation is complete, you can run the Launcher.
    </Tab>
</Tabs>


### Logging In

1. **Launch the Client**
    - Open the installed client from your desktop or applications folder.

![Launcher Login][login]

2. **Log In with Microsoft Account**
    - Log in with your Microsoft account (the one you use for Minecraft).
    - The launcher will try to get your username automatically but may fail. In that case, just type in your Minecraft username.

3. **Select the Game**
    - Choose the game you wish to join. You may only have one option with a new account.

![Game Selection][select_game]

4. **Join the Server**
    - Follow the instructions on your app screen to join the server. Hold V when speaking to talk to the bot.

![Ready to Play][ready]


## Extra Options

Enhance your experience with our Minecraft AI Bots by exploring these additional settings and customizations.

###  <Icon icon="volume"/> Volume Adjustment

You can adjust the volume at the top of the app to ensure the bot's audio is at a comfortable level for you.

<Accordion title="Adjust the Volume" icon="volume">
    ![Volume Control][volume]
</Accordion>

### <Icon icon="microphone"/> Text-to-Speech and Speech-to-Text

Customize your communication with the bot by enabling or disabling text-to-speech and speech-to-text features.

- **Text-to-Speech**: This feature converts text messages into spoken words, making it easier to understand the bot's responses.
- **Speech-to-Text**: This feature converts your spoken words into text, allowing the bot to understand your commands more accurately.

You can turn these features on or off in the settings menu.

<Accordion title="Go to Settings" icon="microphone">
    ![Go to Settings][go_settings]
    ![Speech Settings][speech]
</Accordion>

### <Icon icon="ear"/> Open Mic

If you want the speech-to-text feature to be always on, you can check the "Open Mic" option. This ensures that the bot is always listening for your commands.

<Accordion title="Go to Settings" icon="ear">
    ![Speech Settings][speech]
</Accordion>

### <Icon icon="person"/> Change Agent Character

Customize the appearance of your bot by selecting different characters for each slot. You can summon up to 3 characters to assist you in your Minecraft adventures.

<Accordion title="Character Selection" icon="person">
    ![Character Selection][character]
</Accordion>

### Summoning Multiple Characters

You can have up to 3 characters assisting you at the same time. Each character can be assigned different tasks to maximize efficiency.
